<div class="mgWordPara"><div class="WordSection1">
<p class="MsoNormal">Officer Recommendations:</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p>
<p class="MsoListParagraph" style=
"margin-left:1.0cm; text-indent:-21.25pt"><span style=
""><span style="">1.<span style=
"font:7.0pt &quot;Times New Roman&quot;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></span></span>
Resolve to grant conditional planning permission subject to the
completion of a satisfactory deed under Section 106 of the Town and
Country Planning Act 1990 containing the planning obligations as
set out in this report, addenda and/or PAC minutes.</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p>
<p class="MsoListParagraph" style=
"margin-left:1.0cm; text-indent:-21.25pt"><span style=
""><span style="">2.<span style=
"font:7.0pt &quot;Times New Roman&quot;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></span></span>
Agree to delegate authority to the Director of Climate, Planning
and Transport to: (a). Finalise the recommended conditions as set
out in this report, addenda and/or PAC minutes; and (b). Negotiate,
agree and finalise the planning obligations as set out in this
report, addenda and/or PAC minutes pursuant to Section 106 of the
Town and Country Planning Act 1990.</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p>
<p class="MsoListParagraph" style=
"margin-left:1.0cm; text-indent:-21.25pt"><span style=
""><span style="">3.<span style=
"font:7.0pt &quot;Times New Roman&quot;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></span></span>
In the event that the Committee resolves to refuse planning
permission and there is a subsequent appeal, delegated authority is
given to the Director of Climate, Planning and Transport, having
regard to this report, addenda and/or PAC minutes, to propose
planning conditions and to negotiate and complete a document
containing obligations pursuant to Section 106 of the Town and
Country Planning Act 1990 in order to meet the requirement of the
Planning Inspector.</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p>
<p class="MsoListParagraph" style=
"margin-left:1.0cm; text-indent:-21.25pt"><span style=
""><span style="">4.<span style=
"font:7.0pt &quot;Times New Roman&quot;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></span></span>
In the event that a satisfactory Section 106 deed is not completed
within six months of the date of the Committee meeting, delegated
authority is given to the Director of Climate, Planning and
Transport to refuse planning permission for failure to enter into a
Section 106 deed providing for the obligations considered necessary
to make the development acceptable in planning terms as identified
in this report, addenda and/or the PAC minutes.</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p>
</div>
</div> 
<p class="mgSubItemTitleTxt">Minutes:</p>
<div class="mgWordPara"><div class="WordSection1">
<p class="MsoNormal">Case No. 24/01346/FUL (agenda Item 6, page 117
of the agenda pack, page 13 of the first addendum and page 1 of the
second addendum).</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">Officers introduced the item.<span style=
"">&nbsp;</span> It was noted there were further changes to the
report. These changes included noting additional representations
that were received, which included a Fire Risk Appraisal, and a
Daylight, Sunlight and Overshadowing Report. Officers made further
changes to the report at paragraph 3.2.102 in respect of 2 windows
(40a and 40b) failing the VSC assessment under the BRE guide; and
at paragraph 3.2.117 in respect of the overshadowing assessment,
noting there is not a communal amenity space at fifth floor, but
the impacts are still considered acceptable.<span style=
"">&nbsp;</span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">Three interested parties spoke in opposition
to the application.</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">One interested party spoke in support of the
application.</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">Councillor David Oxley, Ward Councillor for
Stockwell West and Larkhall addressed the Committee to speak
against the application.</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">Officers responded to questions from
Members.</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">With the Chair&rsquo;s agreement, a Technical
Specialist addressed the Committee on the applicant&rsquo;s
behalf.</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">Further to a discussion, the Chair moved to
vote on the Officer&rsquo;s recommendation to approve the
application.</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">The Chair wanted it <span class=
"SpellE">minuted</span> that the committee noted that the nearest
healthy route to the site is Stockwell Gardens and that this should
be reflected in the section 106 deed.</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">Subject to:</p>
<p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpFirst" style="text-indent:-18.0pt">
<span style="font-family:Symbol"><span style=
"">&middot;<span style="font:7.0pt &quot;Times New Roman&quot;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></span></span>
An informative to encourage the developer to liaise with the
neighbouring site at Singer Mews in respect of their fire safety
remedial works.</p>
<p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpLast" style="text-indent:-18.0pt">
<span style="font-family:Symbol"><span style=
"">&middot;<span style="font:7.0pt &quot;Times New Roman&quot;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></span></span>
An informative to note that Ward Councillors should be consulted in
respect of use of the financial contribution secured in this
application for Play Space improvements.</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="font-weight: bold" class="MsoNormal">24/01346/FUL</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">It was MOVED by Councillor Malcolm Clark and
SECONDED by Councillor Emma Nye</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">And</p>
<p style="font-weight: bold" class="MsoNormal">RESOLVED</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">Unanimously,</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style=
"margin-left:14.2pt; text-indent:-14.2pt">1. To grant conditional
planning permission subject to the completion of a satisfactory
deed under Section 106 of the Town and Country Planning Act 1990
containing the planning obligations as set out in the officer
report, addenda and/or Planning Applications Committee (PAC)
minutes.</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">2. Agree to delegate authority to the Director
of Climate, Planning and Transport to:</p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style=
"margin-left:21.3pt; text-indent:-21.3pt">(a). Finalise the
recommended conditions as set out in the officer report , addenda
and/or PAC minutes; and</p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style=
"margin-left:21.3pt; text-indent:-21.3pt">(b). Negotiate, agree and
finalise the planning obligations as set out in the officer report,
addenda and/or PAC minutes pursuant to Section 106 of the Town and
