completion of a satisfactory deed under Section 106 of the Town and
Country Planning Act 1990 containing the planning obligations as
set out in this report, addenda and/or PAC minutes.</p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-left:18.0pt">&nbsp;</p>
<p class="MsoListParagraph" style=
"margin-left:1.0cm; text-indent:-21.25pt"><span style=
""><span style="">2.<span style=
"font:7.0pt &quot;Times New Roman&quot;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></span></span>
Agree to delegate authority to the Director of Climate Change,
Planning and Transport to: (a). Finalise the recommended conditions
as set out in this report, addenda and/or PAC minutes; and (b).
Negotiate, agree and finalise the planning obligations as set out
in this report, addenda and/or PAC minutes pursuant to Section 106
of the Town and Country Planning Act 1990.</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p>
<p class="MsoListParagraph" style=
"margin-left:1.0cm; text-indent:-21.25pt"><span style=
""><span style="">3.<span style=
"font:7.0pt &quot;Times New Roman&quot;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></span></span>
In the event that the Committee resolves to refuse planning
permission and there is a subsequent appeal, delegated authority is
given to the Director of Climate Change, Planning and Transport,
having regard to this report, addenda and/or PAC minutes, to
propose planning conditions and to negotiate and complete a
document containing obligations pursuant to Section 106 of the Town
and Country Planning Act 1990 in order to meet the requirement of
the Planning Inspector.</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p>
<p class="MsoListParagraph" style=
"margin-left:1.0cm; text-indent:-21.25pt"><span style=
