<p class="mgSubItemTitleTxt">Minutes:</p>
<div class="mgWordPara"><div class="WordSection1">
<p class="MsoNormal">Case No. 24/02054/FUL (agenda Item 5, page 45
of the agenda pack, page 1 of the first addendum).</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">Officers introduced the item. It was noted
that Officers received an additional letter of support from Trinity
Baptist Church, who were the current occupants of the site. There
would be an increase to the employment and Skills contribution
secured in the section 106 deed, rising from &pound;13,000 as
reported to &pound;18,135. It was also proposed there be an
amendment to condition 18, which would ensure that the green roof
was secured in perpetuity.</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">One interested party spoke in support of the
application.</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">Officers responded to questions from
Members.</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">Further to a discussion, the Chair moved to
vote on the Officer&rsquo;s recommendation to approve the
application.</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">The Chair wanted it <span class=
"SpellE">minuted</span> that the Committee was interested in
condition 12, the details of the play space and wanted to ensure
that it would be well designed and utilised.</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">Subject to:</p>
<p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpFirst" style="text-indent:-18.0pt">
<span style="font-family:Symbol"><span style=
"">&middot;<span style="font:7.0pt &quot;Times New Roman&quot;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></span></span>
An amendment to condition 18 which would ensure that the green roof
was secured in perpetuity.</p>
<p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpLast" style="text-indent:-18.0pt">
<span style="font-family:Symbol"><span style=
"">&middot;<span style="font:7.0pt &quot;Times New Roman&quot;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></span></span>
An informative was requested to ensure that, when the applicant
submits the detailed designs for the layout of the community space,
these demonstrate that the space would be suitable for a wide range
of community uses, including the provision of facilities such as
toilets and a kitchen.</p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-left:18.0pt">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="font-weight: bold" class="MsoNormal">24/02054/FUL</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">It was MOVED by Councillor Malcolm Clark and
SECONDED by Councillor Diogo Costa</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">And</p>
<p style="font-weight: bold" class="MsoNormal">RESOLVED</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">Unanimously,</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style=
"margin-left:14.2pt; text-indent:-14.2pt">1. To grant conditional
planning permission subject to the completion of a satisfactory
deed under Section 106 of the Town and Country Planning Act 1990
containing the planning obligations as set out in this report,
addenda and/or PAC minutes.</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">2. Agree to delegate authority to the Director
of Climate Change, Planning and Transport to:</p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style=
"margin-left:21.3pt; text-indent:-21.3pt">(a). Finalise the
recommended conditions as set out in the officer report, addenda
and/or PAC minutes; and</p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style=
"margin-left:21.3pt; text-indent:-21.3pt">(b). Negotiate, agree and
finalise the planning obligations as set out in the officer report,
addenda and/or PAC minutes pursuant to Section 106 of the Town and
Country Planning Act 1990.</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style=
"margin-left:14.2pt; text-indent:-14.2pt">3. In the event that a
satisfactory Section 106 deed is not completed within six months of
the date of the Committee meeting, delegated authority is given to
the Director of Climate Change, Planning and Transport to refuse
planning permission for failure to enter into a Section 106 deed
providing for the obligations considered necessary to make the
development acceptable in planning terms as identified in the
officer report, addenda and/or the PAC minutes.</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p>
</div>
