Planning Inspector.</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p>
<p class="MsoListParagraph" style=
"margin-left:1.0cm; text-indent:-21.25pt"><span style=
""><span style="">4.<span style=
"font:7.0pt &quot;Times New Roman&quot;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></span></span>
In the event that a satisfactory Section 106 deed is not completed
within six months of the date of the Committee meeting, delegated
authority is given to the Director of Climate, Planning and
Transport to refuse planning permission for failure to enter into a
Section 106 deed providing for the obligations considered necessary
to make the development acceptable in planning terms as identified
in this report, addenda and/or the PAC minutes.</p>
</div>
</div> 
<p class="mgSubItemTitleTxt">Minutes:</p>
<div class="mgWordPara"><div class="WordSection1">
<p class="MsoNormal">Case No. 25/02646/FUL (agenda Item 7, page 201
of the agenda pack, page 17 of the first addendum and page 2 of the
second addendum).</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">Officers introduced the item.</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">One interested party spoke in support of the
application.</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">Councillor Ibtisam Adem, Ward Councillor for
Knights Hill addressed the Committee to speak on the
application.</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">Officers responded to questions from
Members.</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">With the Chair&rsquo;s agreement, a Registered
Speaker and Technical Specialist addressed the Committee on the
applicant&rsquo;s behalf.</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">The Chair asked for it to be <span class=
"SpellE">minuted</span> that the Committee referenced strong
feelings around the need for speed reduction measures and
preference for a speed camera, and that Officers should continue
their work with the police.</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">Further to a discussion, the Chair moved to
vote on the Officer&rsquo;s recommendation to approve the
application.</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="font-weight: bold" class="MsoNormal">25/02646/FUL</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">It was MOVED by Councillor Malcolm Clark and
SECONDED by Councillor Diogo Costa</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">And</p>
<p style="font-weight: bold" class="MsoNormal">RESOLVED</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">Unanimously,</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style=
"margin-left:14.2pt; text-indent:-14.2pt">1. To grant conditional
planning permission subject to the completion of a satisfactory
deed under Section 106 of the Town and Country Planning Act 1990
containing the planning obligations as set out in the officer
report, addenda and/or PAC minutes.</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">2. Agree to delegate authority to the Director
of Climate, Planning and Transport to:</p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style=
"margin-left:21.3pt; text-indent:-21.3pt">(a). Finalise the
recommended conditions as set out in the officer report, addenda
and/or PAC minutes; and</p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style=
"margin-left:21.3pt; text-indent:-21.3pt">(b). Negotiate, agree and
finalise the planning obligations as set out in the officer report,
addenda and/or PAC minutes pursuant to Section 106 of the Town and
Country Planning Act 1990.</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style=
"margin-left:14.2pt; text-indent:-14.2pt">3. In the event that a
satisfactory Section 106 deed is not completed within six months of
the date of the Committee meeting, delegated authority is given to
the Director of Climate, Planning and Transport to refuse planning
permission for failure to enter into a Section 106 deed providing
for the obligations considered necessary to make the development
acceptable in planning terms as identified in the officer report,
addenda and/or the PAC minutes.</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p>
</div>
</div> 
					
