months of the date of the Committee meeting, delegated authority is
given to the Director of Climate, Planning and Transport to refuse
planning permission for failure to enter into a Section 106 deed
providing for the obligations considered necessary to make the
development acceptable in planning terms as identified in this
report, addenda and/or the PAC minutes.</p>
</div>
